stylometry: Safety stock is the amount of extra stock between order points. The concept of safety stock is to prevent a stock-out. It important to have, because if out demand exceeds our expectations, then we have enough to support that extra demand until our next order is in. If we expected to not order more inventory for awhile and all of the sudden our demand shoots up, we have that safety stock to support that demand and give us hopefully enough time to place an order to get more inventory.
